With a growing amount of users on a system, it's good practice to ensure the user/group/role structure is efficiently managed.

System admins may want to prevent project admins from adding individual users to project roles, only allowing groups. This helps ensure consistency of user permissions across teams/projects.

So if an user wants access to project, they need to be added to the appropriate group that has been granted the proper roles/perms
